  + [low_resolution_signal] is geometric depletion of vortex stretching
  + [bounded_question] is which alignment, strain, or vorticity direction conditions imply regularity, and whether any are propagated by the equations rather than assumed

& [SourceSet] is research evidence
  + [source_001] is Constantin and Fefferman vorticity direction criterion lineage
    = evidence: regularity can follow when vorticity direction has sufficient coherence, motivating geometric depletion of vortex stretching
  + [source_002] is Giga, Gu, and Hsu "Continuous alignment of vorticity direction prevents the blow-up..."
    = url: https://eprints.lib.hokudai.ac.jp/repo/huscap/all/73710/ContinuousAlignmentVorticity.pdf
    = evidence: uniform continuity of vorticity direction can rule out type I blowup in bounded domains under no-slip conditions
  + [source_003] is Hou "The Dual Role of Convection in 3D Navier-Stokes Equations"
    = url: https://www.dam.brown.edu/AFOSR_MURI_pub/FoCM_Hou_new_dual.pdf
    = evidence: local geometric regularity of the unit vorticity vector can deplete vortex stretching; computations show dynamic depletion in vortex-tube scenarios
  + [source_004] is "On Depletion of the Vortex-Stretching Term in the 3D Navier-Stokes Equations"
    = url: https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s00220-004-1072-0
    = evidence: cancellation properties in the vortex-stretching term lead to geometric criteria preventing finite-time blowup
  + [source_005] is Beirao da Veiga and Berselli direction-of-vorticity survey line
    = url: https://people.dm.unipi.it/beiraodaveiga/pdf/hbv-127.pdf
    = evidence: Holder continuity assumptions on vorticity direction imply integrability/regularity conclusions

& [Finding] is the geometric depletion boundary
  + [known_shape] is vorticity-direction coherence, strain alignment, or geometric regularity can be sufficient for regularity
